It was when I had nothing to lose that I ended up creating something more beautiful than I set out to make! Don’t let a failed painting be the end. Just because it’s not going the way you planned, doesn’t mean it’s beauty isn’t there. Give yourself the freedom to play and try something new! You never know what you’ll find! #resinart #oceanart #midnight #dontgiveup #trynewthings #resintutorial

Trust the process friends!!!! Sanding my resin art is always so nerve racking! But pouring the top coat brings it back to life and creates a shine even better than before! 🤩 So if you saw my reel yesterday then you know that all of the black resin slid right off of this midnight ocean. I’m sad I stopped recording because once I realized it was messed up and I would have to redo it, I allowed myself the freedom to play. I picked the resin up off the floor and drizzled it back on. I ran my fingers through it and ended up creating an even better ocean than I set out to! Remember friends, it’s not done until it’s good. And if you allow yourself to play and enjoy your art, then beauty will be the result. (Kind of like in life 😘) Keep going. You’ve got this. 
#resinart #resinartist #oceanart #beachlife #midnight #keepgoing #trusttheprocess #resintutorial

Learning new skills can be daunting. I have been taking my own advice on if you want to do something then take a class and learn it! 5 years ago?!? This is where it all started. Our home flooded in Hurricane Harvey that hit Galveston - Houston in August 2017. I had been painting with watercolors and had the beginnings of my art career, but when my home was destroyed I no longer had a space to create. So while our home was rebuilt (by my awesome husband) I would de-stress by watching videos of acrylic pour painting. I was obsessed and desperately wanted to figure it out. No one really shared their secrets at that point so it was a bit of trial and error. I wanted a piece to resemble the sunrise and this is it! I saw others adding a top coat of resin for shine, and when I added it, the real obsession began! I’ve worked hard learning to work with resin and have enjoyed this medium tremendously! When I look at this painting close up, I see so many flaws and air bubbles, but it still hangs in my living room. It’s a constant reminder of how tragedy struck, but God renewed. Had my home never flooded, I don’t know if I would have discovered resin art. Maybe I would have, but I sure like the way it came into my life.

Take a deep breath my friend and enjoy the golden lava. Breath in the peace and rest your body needs and breath out your anxiety. The God that created you is calling you by name. He said He will carry your burden, so give it to Him. Then let His Spirit fill yours, just like the gold fills the cracks. #asmr #sosatisfying #peaceandrest #faithart #geodeart #agate #mixedmedia
Sometimes I just have to look back over my art that I’ve had the opportunity to create in the past. It makes me extremely hopeful for what will be created in the future.

Hi friend. I’m slowly getting back into the groove of creating now that my kids are back to school. I’ve spent the summer working on learning a few new skills but to be honest, it’s harder than I expected. I have ideas that I don’t know how to make happen and it’s a challenge that I love and am intimidated by all at the same time. So, I’ll keep following my own advice that I tell you all the time: just keep trying. I’ll keep working towards my ideas and I know I’ll eventually get it. So friend, if you’re struggling to get the art to look like what’s in your head, know you aren’t alone. Keep trying and I know you’ll get it.

A new day starts in the dark… isn’t that the truth! After ignoring and pushing down some childhood trauma, I finally faced it and God healed my heart through group therapy back in 2014. God then restored art into my life like a faucet that got turned back on full blast. Watercolor was my medium then. Then tragedy struck again and we flooded in Hurricane Harvey in 2017. Without a space to create, I found myself zoning out to videos of artist pouring their paint. I was obsessed. I decided to try it when I was ready to decorate my living room. Then I put a top coat of resin on top and was instantly hooked on resin! It took some dark days in my life to find my art passion but it definitely was the start to a new day in my life. I’m forever grateful for God’s gift of art in my life.

I’ve had the idea to layer my painting like this for quite a while, so I’m really excited to finally have made it happen! I’m praying it brings in a significant donation and that whoever gets it will always be reminded that even under the pressure of life, we are not crushed. Let your life be transformed by the love of God. He is for you and with you, especially in the dark times. #geodeart #agate #metamorphosis #resinart #customart #crystals

Live Color Full = Live Your Life Full of Color! Life is a beautiful journey. It’s full of extreme highs and even more extreme lows, but there is always beauty in all of it. When I finally take my focus off of the immediate problems, I am able to set my eyes on God and how He is with me and carrying me through. That is when I can see the treasure in the darkness. That is when I can have joy in the midst of sorrow. That is when I can have peace that doesn’t make sense. Seek the Lord my friends. He will fill your heart to overflowing. 
#abstractart #livecolorfull #beautyfromashes #resin #neon

Honored to have my art piece, “Washed in the Blood”, on display at Webster Presbyterian Church. Even more excited to share the exhibit with my mom and daughter! My mom’s paintings is of my sister in her wedding dress and my daughter’s digital art is of her original characters dancing. If you’re local to the Webster area, you should definitely go check out the art show. There are so many talented artist’s works on display!

Why do I create art that resembles geodes? Because I feel like my life is like a geode. Instead of being crushed and destroyed by the hard things I had to walk through, God used it to transform my life. When I finally faced the pain and let God heal my heart, He was faithful to restore what was stolen from me. One of those gifts of restoration was art and creativity. It’s a gift I don’t take for granted. My prayer for you today is that you have the opportunity to face the pain and allow God to come in and heal your heart. It is typically not an easy thing to do but it is worth it. There is freedom from the pain. There is healing over past experiences (HOPE). The God that created you wants to heal you.

Do you feel broken? Let the healing power of God fill the empty crevices with His healing power. There is H.O.P.E. Healing Over Past Experiences. I’m praying for you today friend. Ezekiel 34 is one of my absolute favorite passages. God is mad at the ones He left in charge. They have failed the people. They have abused those they were supposed to protect. So God steps up and declares that He alone will be our Shepherd. “I will demand My flock from them.” (verse 10) Then He declares how He will provide, protect and bless His people. People will fail us but God never will. 
#ezekiel34 #hope #healing #mixedmedia #resinart

What part of your process intimidates you? Remix or comment and let me know. Sanding used to be incredibly intimidating when I started. I didn’t get it right at first and had to redo my sanding process multiple times. But now I find it therapeutic. The hum of the sander is peaceful and I can think or pray through things. Don’t let fear stop you from being creative. If you have the creative idea, jump in and figure it out. I believe in you friend.
